    public abstract class ReferenceEntity
extends HibernatingEntity
implements INaturallyKeyedEntity, java.lang.Cloneable
    For reference entities which have no natural scope from the domain model. Purpose: An abstract class for persistent domain entities that are scope-limited (for example, in argo by yard, facility, complex, or operator). The natural key of such entities must be unique within its scope, and whenever a new one is created, its scope must be defined (identified as an association to a EntitySet entity). Finally, no update should change the scope of an entity. This class enforces these requirements.
    Author:
    Jon Shields Date: Mar 9, 2004
